displaytitle: Venus and Cupid (Sine Cerere et Baccho friget Venus)
dimensions: plate (sheet trimmed to plate): 9.4 cm (3 11/16 in.)
creditline: Bequest of Junius S. Morgan, Class of 1888
inscribed:
One line of Latin in margin: SINE CERERE ET BACcHO FRIGET VENUS [in the word BACcHO the small c is inscribed in the capital C].

Inscribed in clouds, upper center: y 4 [not mentioned in Hollstein]

Signed in plate, lower left: HG I
